mage time. Schema [reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json](../metadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json) (a vendored copy of the upstream GraalVM schema), with top-level keys `reflection`, `jni`, `resources`, `bundles`, `serialization`, and `foreignCalls`. Every entry must carry a `condition.typeReachable` clause (FR-M-2) so the plugin can rely on conditional registration. The legacy split-config layout (`reflect-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, …) is no longer present.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:201:- **FR-M-1** Metadata files contain only JSON entries described by GraalVM's manual-configuration reference. Native-image properties (`native-image.properties`) and other build-time tweaks are forbidden — by default every library is runtime-initialized.\n./stats/org.wildfly.openssl/wildfly-openssl-java/2.0.0.Alpha1/execution-metrics.json:106:      \"metadata_file\": \"metadata/org.wildfly.openssl/wildfly-openssl-java/2.0.0.Alpha1/reachability-metadata.json\"\n./stats/dev.zio/zio-internal-macros_2.13/2.0.22/execution-metrics.json:53:      \"metadata_file\": \"metadata/dev.zio/zio-internal-macros_2.13/2.0.22/reachability-metadata.json\"\n./stats/io.prometheus/simpleclient_caffeine/0.16.0/execution-metrics.json:53:      \"metadata_file\": \"metadata/io.prometheus/simpleclient_caffeine/0.16.0/reachability-metadata.json\"\n./stats/dev.zio/zio-http_3/3.3.3/execution-metrics.json:47:      \"metadata_file\": \"metadata/dev.zio/zio-http_3/3.3.3/reachability-metadata.json\"\n./stats/io.prometheus/simpleclient/0.16.0/execution-metrics.json:53:      \"metadata_file\": \"metadata/io.prometheus/simpleclient/0.16.0/reachability-metadata.json\"\n./stats/dev.zio/zio-logging_2.13/2.4.0/execution-metrics.json:53:      \"metadata_file\": \"metadata/dev.zio/zio-logging_2.13/2.4.0/reachability-metadata.json\"\n./stats/io.prometheus/simpleclient_tracer_otel_agent/0.16.0/execution-metrics.json:53:      \"metadata_file\": \"metadata/io.prometheus/simpleclient_tracer_otel_agent